            <p><span style="font-weight:bold; color:#b701eb">Purple Haze</span></p>
            <p> Ten years in the making Purple Haze is a very unique strain and this version is available nowhere else in the world. Developed in NZ especially for the NZ climate it is bred from old school heirloom seeds from Thailand taken to Holland in 1982 and given to me ten years ago. These were crossed to another unique farmhouse strain from the Hmong highland Laos tribe people. After five years of searching for a suitable candidate and 400 plants later the Thai hybrid was crossed to a very special mango flavoured Haze.  </p>
     
          <hr>

        
            <div style="float:right; margin:0 15px 5px 5px;">
           <%= link_to image_tag("purplehaze3-thumb.jpg"), "assets/purplehaze3.jpg", :rel => "lightbox", :alt => "", :title => "click to enlarge"%></div>
           
            <p>The Haze side was first bred in California then refined in Holland and Switzerland before coming to me five years ago. It adds more flavour and faster effect to the lovely mild lemon Thai hybrid. The plant grows tall and fast with good disease and pest resistance and unlike many cannabis plants you can easily tell when its ripe because it turns purple and drops it's leaves leaving only the flower buds.  </p>
     
          <hr>

            <div style="float:left; margin:0 15px 5px 5px;">
           <%= link_to image_tag("purplehaze7-thumb.jpg"), "assets/purplehaze7.jpg", :rel => "lightbox", :alt => "", :title => "click to enlarge"%></div>
           
            <p>Purple Haze is a lovely strain with the scent of mango and lavender with just a bite of lemon to it. It is not too strong but not weak either and has a soothing mellow effect while keeping energy and creativity levels high.</p>

            <p> This is a highly recommended medical strain that is much sought after in overseas dispensaries.  </p>
     
